text: San Yu Htwe (born 14 October 1986) is a female Burmese recurve archer from Mindat.http://www.chinlandguardian.com/index.php/news/item/2305-chin-athletes- to-compete-in-sea-games-in-singapore She competed in the archery competition at the 2016 Summer Olympics in Rio de Janeiro, where she ranked at #51 in the ranking round. She defeated Taru Kuoppa in the first round and Mackenzie Brown in the second round but lost to the then current Olympic Champion Ki Bo-bae in the third round.http://www.mmtimes.com/index.php/sports/18707-san-yu-htwe- hits-gold.htmlhttp://www.mmtimes.com/index.php/sports/21507-myanmar-archer- aims-for-bulls-eye.html She said that she felt too excited to be competing against the current Olympic Champion that her performance was not as good as she hoped.https://worldarchery.org/news/143220/htwe-san-yu-cements-myanmars- bracket-busting-reputation ==References== ==External links== * * Category:Burmese female archers Category:Living people Category:People from Chin State Category:1986 births Category:Archers at the 2016 Summer Olympics Category:Olympic archers of Myanmar
title: San Yu Htwe
